contentrichtext.text: '''NR''', '''Nr''' or '''nr''' may refer to: == Places == * [[Nauru]] (ISO 3166-1 country code) ** [[.nr]], the country code top-level domain for Nauru * [[North Riding]] of Yorkshire, England * [[Northern Rhodesia]] * [[NR postcode area]] for the area surrounding Norwich, England * [[New Rockford, North Dakota]], USA ==Defense== * [[National Resources Division]], the domestic division of the United States Central Intelligence Agency * [[Naval Reserve (disambiguation)]], various bodies * [[Naval Reactors]], the governing body of the United States Navy Nuclear Power Program == Others == * [[Nanorod]] * [[National Rail]], a generic term for most passenger rail in the United Kingdom * [[National Review]], an American political magazine * [[Natural rubber]], rubber extracted from Hevea Brasiliensis * [[Networked Robotics Corporation]] * [[New Right (Netherlands)]], a former Dutch political party * [[Noise reduction]] * [[Northern Rock]], a United Kingdom bank * [[Norwegian Computing Center]] (NR, in Norwegian: Norsk Regnesentral) * Not Rated, when referring to a lack of an [[MPAA rating system#Other miscellaneous film ratings|MPAA]] or [[Entertainment Software Rating Board|ESRB]] rating. * [[Nuclear receptor]], a class of receptor proteins in the cell * [[Neutrophil release]] * [[Numerical Recipes]], a series of books on numerical computation (domain "NR.com") * [[Pamir Airways]] (IATA airline designator) * [[Southern Ndebele language]] (ISO 639-1 code) * The logo used by [[Newsround]], a BBC news programme for children == As "Nr." == * The German abbreviation for ''Nummer'', equivalent of the [[Numero sign]] used in English {{disambiguation}}
